<div class="nbunit" id="22Feb1921"><font color="red">22 February 1921</font> (JJ to Harriet Weaver): [clipping from New York Times] Improper novel costs woman $60 Mr Quinn admitted that it was cast in a curious style &hellip; Joyce, he said, didn&apos;t use punctuation marks in this story probably on account of his eyesight</div>
